accessibility.text: Aim: How can we run python programs directly from the shell?
Make sure the file is executable (set correct file permissions).
By default, when you create a file, it is not given any execute permissions.
In order to be able to run your program, you have to turn the execute permissions on.
The owner of a file can always change permissions, regardless of what permissions the owner has. (permissions are about file contents).
